"```sql\nSELECT a.account_id\nFROM account a\nJOIN disp d ON a.account_id = d.account_id\nJOIN client c ON d.client_id = c.client_id\nJOIN district dis ON c.district_id = dis.district_id\nWHERE c.birth_date = (SELECT MAX(birth_date) FROM client)\nAND dis.A11 = (SELECT MAX(dis2.A11) FROM district dis2);\n```\n\nThis SQL query retrieves the account numbers of clients who are the youngest and have the highest average salary. It joins the necessary tables using foreign key relationships and applies conditions to filter the youngest client and the district with the highest average salary."